entries.femaleVariant: I remember you. How've you been?
It's me, Frank. We met during "Icefall." East coast, remember?
Hey, V. It's been ages.
Christ, V, you were supposed to be here an hour ago!
I'm in a rush.
I didn't know you were in Night City. How've you been?
Listen, sorry, uh, in a bit of a rush right now? We'll talk another time, 'kay?
Tell me about Cape Town.
What're people saying about Jenkins?
I need to run.
Tell me about the op in Cape Town.
What does everyone say about Jenkins?
Sure, sure. Good seein' you again.
I see you're busy.
Operation "Cargo." You know about it?
That he's effective. Like any psychopath.
Eh, you know how it is. A week ago, I was still in Cape Town.
V? Everything OK?
Arming local conflicts in Africa? I didn't know that was you.
It was me. We dumped crates full of rifles into the ocean. They had to be pulled out using borrowed fishing boats.
Same old circus, but hey, that's how wars are won.
Apparently, he's gone a little crazier lately.
I heard you're in counterintel. Must have a shitshow on your hands right now after Frankfurt.
Jenkins is your lead, right? Is he what everyone says he is?
We'll talk later.
Agh... Hanging up. I'll be in my office.
Got held up, but I'll be right there.
Fucking Frankfurt... That Abernathy bitch'll probably dump it in our laps.
And you? Who do you work under?
Abernathy. She's really good. Came up with the whole Cape Town ploy on her own.
Abernathy. The bitch who burned my boss on the promotion to Spec Ops Director.
You know how it is. Things happen.
Mhh. They do indeed.
And you hurry up.
Two thousand sixty-seven – an Arasaka bodyguard shields the Emperor of Japan from an assassin's bullet.
Two thousand seventy-one – Arasaka security forces prevent mass riots in San Francisco, saving the city from certain ruin.
Two thousand seventy-four – an Arasaka investigation eliminates a terror cell in Rio de Janeiro, ending a string of attacks and executing those responsible.
Two thousand seventy-six – Arasaka's counterintelligence division effectively secures a corporate summit in Jakarta, foiling forty-five plots to attack and sabotage it.
How will Arasaka shine in two thousand seventy-seven? That depends on you.
Who do you work under?
Hey, he's in a tough spot. The director was supposed to greenlight his promotion when the Japanese arrived. She stabbed him in the back instead.
[Talk]
Give me a holler on the holo sometime, huh?
I got held up.
